value.value: Hamartoma nasal

definition.value: A hamartoma (tissue malformation consisting of an abnormal mixture of constitutive components) originating in the nose.

value.value: Depósitos de lípidos intraneuronales metacromáticos.

A type of metachromasia localized to a peripheral nerve. Metachromasia may be defined as the staining of tissue or tissue components such that the color of the tissue-bound dye complex differs significantly from the color of the original dye complex to give a marked contrast in color. For instance in metachromatic leukodystrophy, bloated Schwann cells, containing granularmetachromatic storage material May display a characteristic yellow green dichroism under crossed polarised light.

definition.value: In metachromatic leukodystrophy, galactosyl sulfatide (cerebroside sulfate) accumulates in the white matter of the CNS and in the peripheral nerves. Galactosyl sulfatide, and to a lesser extent lactosyl sulfatide, also accumulate within the kidney, gallbladder, and certain other visceral organs and are excreted in excessive amounts in the urine. In histologic preparations, they form spherical granular masses that stain metachromatically (i.e., with a color different from that of the dye solution). See Figure 2 of PMID:16291896.

Activity of beta-ureidopropionase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.
Disminución de la actividad de la dihidropirimidinasa hepática.
Activity of dihydropyrimidinase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.
Fontanela hundida
Fontanelle that is more deeply set than normal. Fontanelles are normally relatively firm and curve only slightly inward. A sunken fontanelle can be a sign of dehydration or marasmus.
Angulación del pene
Abnormally increased curvature of the penis.
Historia de procedimiento uretral o cateterismo.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: History of urethral procedure or catheterization

label.value: History of urethral procedure or catheterization

definition.value: A past medical history of a procedure or catheterization involving the urethra.

value.value: Hinchazón del pene
Abormal enlargement of the penis owing to accumulation of fluid.
Reducción de la actividad de la alfa-1,4-glucosidasa muscular.

definition.value: Activity of the enzyme alpha-1,4-glucosidase activity in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Tumor marrón

A brown tumor is a bone lesion that results from bony resorption by excess osteoclastic activity, and replacement by fibrous tissue and giant cells. Brown tumor is an uncommon pathognomonic sign of hyperparathyroidism.
Figuras de llama dérmica

Flame-figures are composed of a central part consisting of collagen fibers and eosinophilic granules, surrounded by a histiocytic and eosinophilic infiltrate. Subsequently, eosinophils tend to disappear and are replaced by phagocytic granulomas, consisting of histiocytes and sometimes giant cells, around the flame figures.

definition.value: Flame figures may be observed in Wells syndrome.

value.value: Exacerbación posparto

definition.value: Applied to a sign or symptom that is present during pregnancy and becomes worse following birth.

value.value: Exposición a retinoides

definition.value: History of having taken retinoids.

value.value: Exposición al propiltiouracilo

definition.value: History of having been treated with propylthiouracil.

value.value: Historia de actividades al aire libre

definition.value: History of spending a substantial amount of time outdoors with occupation or hobbies related to the outdoors, including hunting, gardening, farming, agriculture, horticulture, miners, working in wet fields.

value.value: Drenaje del tracto sinusal en la piel.
A sinus tract is an abnormal channel that originates from the skin or a mucous surface to a deep-seated focus of suppuration.

definition.value: A soft tissue ulcer can show a sinus tract leading to a deeper soft tissue abscess and may occasionally extend to a joint. Chronic osteomyelitis can be associated with a sinus tract and cloaca (opening or rupture of bony cortex overlying an area of osteomyelitis) draining granulation tissue, pus, or necrotic debris from the bone to the skin.

value.value: Antecedentes de trasplante de córnea

definition.value: Past medical history of surgical replacement of the cornea with corneal tissue from a donor.

value.value: Ruptura espontánea de la cápsula del cristalino
Breakage of the capsule of the lens. This is most often observed as a complication of lens surgery, but this term refers to lens capsule rupture not related to surgery or major trauma.

definition.value: Spontaneous lens capsule rupture has been observed with Marshall syndrome.

value.value: Usuario de lentes de contacto
A past medical history of wearing contact lenses.
Engrosamiento de la mucosa de las vías respiratorias
Increase in thickness of the mucosa of the airways above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: This feature can be observed in mucolipidosis type II. Progressive airway thickening can lead to respiratory insufficiency.

value.value: Diferencia de potencial nasal transepitelial hiperpolarizada
Increased (more negative) voltage across the nasal epithelium.

definition.value: The resulting (or basal) potential difference (PD) is negative or polarized (viewed from the epithelial surface) and in normal subjects, it is usually between -15 and -25 mV. The measurement continues by the sequential perfusion of compounds that block inwardly directed sodium transport through inhibition of ENaC (amiloride), followed by augmentation of chloride transport through CFTR. During perfusion of amiloride, the potential difference depolarizes as ENaC transport is reduced, and the PD typically approaches a low polarizing value (typically between 0 and -10 mV).

value.value: Sinequias corneopalpebrales
An adhesion between the conjunctiva of the eyelid and the cornea.
Papiloma intraductal de mama

Intraductal papilloma is a benign tumor found within breast ducts. The abnormal proliferation of ductal epithelial cells causes growth. A solitary intraductal papilloma is usually found centrally posterior to the nipple affecting the central duct. Multiple intraductal papillomas are located peripherally, found in any breast quadrant affecting the peripheral ducts.
Parto abrupto
Precipitous labor is extremely rapid labor and delivery, usually defined as expulsion of the fetus within less than 3 hours of commencement of regular contractions.
Embarazo gemelar
Maternal history of a pregnancy with two fetuses in the uterus.
Masa vaginal

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the vagina. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Dolor en el ángulo costovertebral
Pain that is elicited by palpation of the region inside of the costovertebral angle, which is formed by the 12th rib and the spine.

definition.value: Costovertebral angle tenderness can be observed with conditions including pyelonephritis and ureteral stones.

value.value: Sensibilidad al movimiento cervical

Pain that is elicited by moving the uterine cervix. This finding can be ascertained by pelvic exam. Cervical motion tenderness is a gynecological exam finding that could be indicative of peritoneal infection.
Secreción anormal del pene

definition.value: Fluid that originates from the urethra that is not urine, pre-ejaculate or semen.

value.value: Pliegue supernumerario de flexión de los dedos
The presence of an extra digital crease in and individual with normal joint anatomy.
Predominio en articulaciones grandes

definition.value: Refers to a phenotypic abnormality that mainly affect large joints.

value.value: Monoarticular

definition.value: Refers to a phenotypic abnormality that affects a single joint.

value.value: Pliegue palmar en forma de palo de hockey
An abnormality of the upper palmar crease whereby the crease widens and ends between the second and third fingers and is said to resemble a hockey stick.

definition.value: See figure 5 of PMID:29094891.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de succiniladenosina en orina
The amount of succinyladenosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento del nivel de 5-hidroximetiluracilo en orina

definition.value: The amount of 5-hydroxymethyluracil in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Disminución del nivel de creatinina en orina.

definition.value: The amount of creatinine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de desoxiuridina en orina

definition.value: The amount of deoxyuridine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de dihidrouracilo en orina
The amount of dihydrouracil in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento del nivel de dihidrotimina en orina

definition.value: The amount of dihydrothymine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de sulfatida en orina

definition.value: The amount of sulfatides in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal. Sulfatides are derived from GalCer via esterification of a sulfate group to 3-hydroxyl of the galactose moiety.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de ácido xanturénico en orina

definition.value: The amount of xanthurenic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel urinario de oligosacáridos ricos en N-acetilglucosamina

definition.value: Presence of N-acetylglucosamine-rich oligosaccharides in the urine.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de 2'-desoxiadenosina en orina

definition.value: The amount of 2'-deoxyadenosine (dAdo) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Prueba de orina positiva para 2,4-dinitrofenilhidrazina
Positive (abnormal) result of the 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine urine test, which indicates the presence of alpha-ketoacids in the urine.
Aumento del nivel de dolicol urinario

definition.value: The amount of dolichol in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Disminución del nivel de ácidos biliares en la orina.

definition.value: The amount of bile acids in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Cociente creatina/creatinina urinaria elevada
The ratio of creatine to creatinine concentration in the urine is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: This finding is suggestive of a disorder of creatine metabolism.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de timidina urinaria

definition.value: The amount of thymidine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.
